12. Definitions

"You" refers to any individual or entity that exercises the rights granted under this License.
"Software" refers to the Cardinal System and any associated documentation files, including any updates, modifications, or derivatives thereof.
"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software by an entity that meets ANY of the following criteria:
  a) Has annual revenue exceeding $1 million USD
  b) Has a company valuation exceeding $5 million USD
  c) Has raised total funding exceeding $2 million USD
  d) Has monthly active users exceeding 100,000
  e) Is owned, controlled by, or affiliated with any organization meeting these criteria
  f) Is part of a group of affiliated entities that collectively exceed these criteria

"Company Valuation" means the most recent valuation of the entity as determined by:
  a) The latest funding round
  b) Professional valuation assessment
  c) Acquisition price
  d) Public market capitalization
  e) Internal valuation for tax or accounting purposes
  f) Any other formal valuation method

"Total Funding Raised" means the cumulative amount of:
  a) Venture capital investments
  b) Angel investments
  c) Seed funding
  d) Crowdfunding
  e) Government grants (excluding research grants for qualified institutions)
  f) Convertible notes or SAFEs
  g) Private equity investments
  h) Corporate investments
  i) Other forms of external investment or funding

"Monthly Active Users" means the combined total of:
  a) Unique users who interact with any product or service incorporating the Software within a calendar month
  b) Unique viewers/subscribers across streaming platforms (e.g., Twitch, YouTube) where content featuring or created with the Software is distributed
  c) Unique viewers/followers across social media platforms where content featuring or created with the Software is distributed
  d) Unique viewers of video-on-demand content featuring or created with the Software
  e) Subscribers to channels or accounts primarily featuring content created with the Software
  f) Members of communities centered around products or services using the Software

For the purpose of this definition:
  - Numbers are calculated as an average over the previous three months
  - "Unique viewers" on streaming platforms counts anyone watching for more than 1 minute
  - Multiple platforms or channels controlled by the same entity are counted collectively
  - For mixed-content channels, if the Software is featured in more than 20% of content, all channel metrics apply
  - Metrics include both live and archived content
  - Metrics include all geographic regions and platform variants

"Content Platform Metrics" means any of the following that exceed platform-specific thresholds:
  a) Twitch: 
     - Average concurrent viewers over 1,000
     - Channel followers over 50,000
     - Subscriber count over 2,500
  b) YouTube:
     - Channel subscribers over 100,000
     - Average video views over 25,000
     - Watch time over 100,000 hours/month
  c) Other Social Media:
     - Followers/subscribers over 100,000
     - Average post engagement over 10,000
     - Average content views over 50,000

Meeting any Content Platform Metric threshold triggers the commercial license requirement.

"Affiliated Entities" means any group of organizations that are:
  a) Under common control or ownership
  b) Part of the same corporate group
  c) Connected through substantial shared ownership (20% or more)
  d) Operating under shared branding or identity
  e) Collaborating on the relevant product or service

"Qualified Research Institution" means an organization that:
  a) Is formally recognized by appropriate national or international research bodies
  b) Has research as its primary organizational mission
  c) Derives at least 80% of their funding from research grants, government funding, or educational endowments
  d) Operates on a non-profit basis
  e) Publishes research findings in peer-reviewed journals or equivalent academic venues
  f) Is not primarily engaged in commercial activities or product development

"Commercial Use Assessment" means:
  a) Companies must assess their status against the thresholds quarterly
  b) Any quarter where thresholds are exceeded triggers the commercial license requirement
  c) Once a commercial license is required, it remains required for at least 12 months
  d) Companies must notify Kirigen LLC within 30 days of exceeding any threshold

13. Unreal Engine Integration

13.1 Plugin Status
- This Software is an open source plugin designed specifically for Unreal Engine
- It must be used within the Unreal Engine environment
- It follows Unreal Engine plugin architecture and best practices
- It is subject to Unreal Engine's technical requirements and constraints

13.2 Unreal Engine Compliance
- This Software is designed to work with Unreal Engine and is subject to Epic Games' terms and conditions
- Nothing in this license shall be construed to grant rights to Unreal Engine or Epic Games' intellectual property
- If any portion of this license conflicts with the Unreal® Engine EULA, the Unreal® Engine EULA shall take precedence
- You must maintain compliance with both this license and the Unreal® Engine EULA
- Your use of Unreal Engine features, APIs, and content must comply with Epic Games' licensing requirements
- Any redistribution must comply with Epic Games' distribution requirements for plugins

13.3 Plugin Distribution
- Distribution through the Unreal Engine Marketplace requires additional agreements
- Distribution must follow Epic Games' plugin packaging guidelines
- Plugin versioning must align with supported Unreal Engine versions
- Documentation must clearly state Unreal Engine version compatibility
- Support for different Unreal Engine versions is at Kirigen LLC's discretion

13.4 Integration Requirements
- The Software must be used as a plugin within a valid Unreal Engine installation
- Integration with other engines or standalone use is not permitted
- Modifications must maintain compatibility with Unreal Engine architecture
- Custom builds must comply with Unreal Engine build system requirements
- Third-party dependencies must be compatible with Unreal Engine licensing

